Polviews with Age, Income, Education, and an Interaction Between Who R Voted For and Incumbency

interaction_model_wo_year <- glm(polviews ~ age + income + educ + pres * incumbency, data = gss, family = binomial)
summary(interaction_model_wo_year)
## 
## Call:
## glm(formula = polviews ~ age + income + educ + pres * incumbency, 
##     family = binomial, data = gss)
##

gss$predicted_prob_wo_year <- predict(interaction_model_wo_year, type = "response")
gss$predicted_class_wo_year <- ifelse(gss$predicted_prob_wo_year > 0.5, 1, 0)

roc_wo_year <- roc(polviews ~ predicted_prob_wo_year, data = gss)
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
roc_wo_year$auc
## Area under the curve: 0.8251
plot(roc_wo_year)

conf_matrix_wo_year <- confusionMatrix(
  data = as.factor(gss$predicted_class_wo_year),
  reference = as.factor(gss$polviews)
)

Polviews with Age, Income, Education, Year, and an Interaction Between Who R Voted For and Incumbency
